  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT333-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">“aṟattoṭu niṟpal” eṉak kiḻattikkut tōḻi uraittatu. </p>


        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">The confidante telling HER: “I will stand firm in duty”. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT333">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> kuṟumpaṭaip pakaḻik koṭuviṟ kāṉavaṉ</l>
          <l> puṉamuṇṭu kaṭinta paiṅkaṇ yāṉai</l>
          <l> naṟuntaḻai makaḷi rōppuṅ kiḷḷaiyoṭu</l>
          <l> kuṟumpoṟaik kaṇavuṅ kuṉṟa nāṭaṉ</l>
          <l> paṇikkuṟai varuttam vīṭat</l>
          <l> tuṇiyi levaṉō tōḻinam maṟaiyē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>If I resolve,</l>
          <l rend="indent">that the suffering should be destroyed,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">[which results] from the lack of action of the man from the hills,</l>
          <l rend="indent">where the fresh-eyed elephant, chased away,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">since he ate from the fields, by the man of the forest</l>
          <l rend="indent3">with bent bow [and] arrows, short weapons  <note place="foot"> What is added here by <term xml:lang="ta"> paṭai </term> DEDR 3860 "army, crowd, weapons, battle"? Is it an apposition to <term xml:lang="ta"> pakaḻi </term> or another thing? Or should we prefer the verbal root <term xml:lang="ta"> paṭai-ttal </term> DEDR 3853 "to create, form, produce" ("arrows formed short")? </note> ,</l>
          <l rend="indent">is lifting [his] head to the short height, together</l>
          <l rend="indent2">with parakeets that women with fragrant foliage scare away,</l>
          <l rend="indent6">– what, friend, [will become] of our secret?</l>

          <lg type="alternate" sameAs="5+6b">
            <l>What [would happen], friend, if I resolved [to give away] the secret,</l>
            <l>so that the suffering is destroyed ...</l>
          </lg>

        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
